lly: the `visit` function adds nodes to `order`, and after reversing, each node is recomputed. The `changed` cell itself is **not** added to `order` (only its dependents are visited). So `changed` is not redundantly recomputed. This is correct.\n\n---\n\n### 17. Dead code: `.gitkeep` file\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/.gitkeep`\n\nThe `.gitkeep` file in the `src/` directory is a placeholder that served its purpose when the directory was initially empty. Now that the directory has actual source files, this file is no longer needed. This is a very minor housekeeping issue, not a code issue.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Confirmed Issues\n\nHere are the definite issues, ordered by severity:\n\n| # | Severity | Category | Description |\n|---|----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | **High** | Visibility | `expandRange` at line 250 of `/workspace/src/index.ts` is public but should be `private` |\n| 2 | **High** | Missing edge case | Unterminated string literals in formulas are silently accepted (lines 28-36 of `/workspace/src/parser.ts`) |\n| 3 | **High** | Missing edge case | Division by zero produces `Infinity`/`NaN` silently instead of an error (line 188 of `/workspace/src/index.ts`) |\n| 4 | **High** | Bug | `MIN()` and `MAX()` on empty ranges return `Infinity` and `-Infinity` respectively (lines 211-218 of `/workspace/src/index.ts`) |\n| 5 | **Medium** | Bug | `evaluateBinop` uses `as number` type assertions without runtime validation, causing silent type coercion for non-numeric operands (lines 182-183 of `/workspace/src/index.ts`) |\n| 6 | **Medium** | Missing edge case | `AVERAGE` of an empty range returns `0` instead of an error (lines 207-210 of `/workspace/src/index.ts`) |\n| 7 | **Low** | Missing edge case | No escape sequence handling in string literals -- impossible to include a double-quote character in a string (lines 28-36 of `/workspace/src/parser.ts`) |\n| 8 | **Low** | Missing feature | No power (`^`) or percent (`%`) operators in the parser |\n| 9 | **Lo